steps:

- press qk (q is used for start recording and k is the shortcut)

- press 0 ( go to start of the line)
- press 2l ( move curser 2 charactar right)
- press x 
- press $
- press p


- press 0 ( go to start of the line)
- press l ( move curser 1 charactar right)
- press x
- press $
- press p

- press 0 ( go to start of the line)
- press x
- press $
- press p

- press q

now the macro is recorded. for run it on all lines in this file:

in normal mode >>> :%normal @k
